caption.title: Parameter estimates from a binomial-error generalized linear mixed effects model for Jamestown Canyon virus detection (1—infected, 0—uninfected) in mosquito samples collected in Connecticut from 2001–2018.
caption.p: Model terms included an offset for pool size, a fixed effect term for trap type, and random intercept effect terms for site, week, and year of collection as well as mosquito species identification.
